✅ Which Event Occurs First?

Event Capturing occurs first.

📌 Complete Event Flow Order:

Whenever an event happens (like a click), it follows three phases:

Capturing Phase ⬇️ (Top → Target)

Target Phase 🎯

Bubbling Phase ⬆️ (Target → Top)

So the correct order is:

Capturing → Target → Bubbling
🧠 Simple Example

If you click a button inside a div:

<div>
  <button>Click Me</button>
</div>

The event travels like this:

document

html

body

div

button (target)

div

body

html

document

⬇️ First it goes down (capturing)
🎯 Reaches target
⬆️ Then it goes up (bubbling)

🚀 Important Note

By default, JavaScript listens in the bubbling phase

Capturing only happens if you explicitly enable it using { capture: true }

🎯 Final Answer:

Event Capturing happens first, then Target phase, then Event Bubbling.